WEBVTT

00:02.393 --> 00:04.091
- Previously on
"Superman and Lois"...

00:04.134 --> 00:05.701
- Let's just focus on what
we came here for, family.

00:05.744 --> 00:07.137
- I came here
with one purpose--

00:07.181 --> 00:09.792
to further
our Kryptonian heritage.

00:09.835 --> 00:12.795
Krypton will finally
be resurrected,

00:12.838 --> 00:15.189
and we'll have
our mother with us.

00:15.232 --> 00:17.930
Help me do that, brother.
- Not like this.

00:17.974 --> 00:19.149
I have to bring back
everyone Edges implanted

00:19.193 --> 00:20.629
with Kryptonian consciousness.

00:20.672 --> 00:21.978
I'll release all my energy
at once.

00:22.022 --> 00:23.284
It'll be enough.

00:23.327 --> 00:24.981
- And you'll be out
of commission for days.

00:25.025 --> 00:25.982
[dramatic music]

00:26.026 --> 00:28.028
- [screams]

00:29.246 --> 00:31.248
- Dad?
- Sarah.

00:31.292 --> 00:35.992
♪

00:54.315 --> 00:56.273
- No, no, no!

00:59.450 --> 01:01.365
What am I supposed to do now?

01:01.409 --> 01:04.368
[soft dramatic music]

01:04.412 --> 01:11.723
♪

01:17.773 --> 01:24.475
♪

01:24.519 --> 01:27.826
[ground crackling and rumbling]

01:41.318 --> 01:44.278
[dramatic music]

01:44.321 --> 01:51.633
♪

02:11.261 --> 02:18.573
♪

02:31.281 --> 02:38.593
♪

02:48.342 --> 02:51.214
[soft dramatic music]

02:51.258 --> 02:58.308
♪

03:07.535 --> 03:10.364
- The day has finally come.

03:10.407 --> 03:14.324
It gives me such joy
to see you here.

03:14.368 --> 03:18.154
- Who are you?
- I am Jor-El.

03:19.416 --> 03:22.245
And you...

03:22.289 --> 03:25.074
you are my son.

03:25.117 --> 03:28.077
[dramatic music]

03:28.120 --> 03:34.997
♪

03:36.216 --> 03:37.739
- What is all this?

03:37.782 --> 03:42.091
- This--this is a place
where you can learn

03:42.134 --> 03:45.529
away from the prying eyes
of the world

03:45.573 --> 03:48.315
lessons about
who you really are

03:48.358 --> 03:50.317
and why you were sent here.

03:50.360 --> 03:52.101
- Sent here from where?

03:52.144 --> 03:56.497
- You were born
on the planet Krypton.

03:56.540 --> 04:00.065
Your true name is Kal,

04:00.109 --> 04:03.895
the last son
from the house of El.

04:03.939 --> 04:05.549
♪

04:05.593 --> 04:07.638
- Why am I so different?

04:07.682 --> 04:09.597
- The Earth's sun.

04:09.640 --> 04:12.382
Your cells
absorb its radiation

04:12.426 --> 04:14.819
in ways humans cannot

04:14.863 --> 04:18.649
creating
nearly endless energy.

04:18.693 --> 04:21.565
Your skin, bones, muscles

04:21.609 --> 04:25.308
all capable
of unimaginable power.

04:25.352 --> 04:28.398
Over time, I will teach you

04:28.442 --> 04:31.967
how to use that power,

04:32.010 --> 04:34.230
that speed,

04:34.274 --> 04:36.711
that strength.

04:36.754 --> 04:39.279
You will learn to do things

04:39.322 --> 04:43.108
you never thought possible
on this Earth.

04:43.152 --> 04:48.375
♪

04:48.418 --> 04:51.378
- Whoo!
[chuckles]

04:51.421 --> 04:53.641
I'm ready, Father.
I can feel it.

04:53.684 --> 04:56.252
- In body and spirit, yes,

04:56.296 --> 04:58.689
but there is something else
you need to learn,

04:58.733 --> 05:01.170
something which I cannot
teach you here.

05:02.432 --> 05:06.044
- What is it?
- Why you wish to help them.

05:09.004 --> 05:10.353
Go.

05:10.397 --> 05:12.137
Reconnect with the world.

05:12.181 --> 05:13.835
Open your heart to them.

05:13.878 --> 05:18.361
Find out why you wish
to be their champion.

05:18.405 --> 05:21.538
[tender orchestral music]

05:21.582 --> 05:27.152
♪

05:27.196 --> 05:29.981
[whooshes]

05:35.160 --> 05:38.120
[tender music]

05:38.163 --> 05:43.255
♪

05:43.299 --> 05:45.649
- Did you find
what you were looking for?

05:47.564 --> 05:49.479
- Yeah.
Yeah, I think so.

05:49.523 --> 05:56.834
♪

06:01.535 --> 06:04.407
I found out who I really am.

06:10.239 --> 06:14.548
I met my Kryptonian father.
- Kryptonian?

06:14.591 --> 06:19.074
- Krypton is my home planet,
Where I'm really from.

06:21.468 --> 06:25.254
I know why I can do
the things I can do, Mom.

06:25.297 --> 06:28.518
I know why
I was sent to Earth--

06:28.562 --> 06:31.869
to be its champion.

06:38.659 --> 06:41.357
- Is that why
you came back home?

06:41.401 --> 06:43.490
To be a hero?

06:43.533 --> 06:47.624
- Yeah, but not yet.

06:47.668 --> 06:50.410
There's someone
I need to see first.

06:52.586 --> 06:55.980
[indistinct chatter]

07:00.507 --> 07:03.640
- Kyle's supposed to be here
any moment.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.599
♪

07:05.642 --> 07:08.340
- Lana!

07:08.384 --> 07:09.516
- Hi.

07:09.559 --> 07:11.779
- Hey, I got some good news.
- What?

07:11.822 --> 07:13.476
- There's an opening
at the fire station.

07:13.520 --> 07:14.825
- [gasps]
- Yeah.

07:14.869 --> 07:17.045
- Oh, that's amazing.
- [laughs]

07:19.439 --> 07:21.441
- Oh, I'm so happy.

07:25.532 --> 07:26.750
Oh, that's awesome.

07:26.794 --> 07:28.491
- It's gonna be huge.
- Yeah.

07:28.535 --> 07:30.232
- [chuckles]
- Let's go in.

07:30.275 --> 07:31.320
- Okay.

07:35.716 --> 07:37.631
- I'm sorry, Clark.

07:39.110 --> 07:41.635
But you were gone a long time.

07:41.678 --> 07:43.637
People move on
with their lives.

07:43.680 --> 07:44.986
- Yeah.

07:46.553 --> 07:50.078
Yeah, I guess so.
- Come with me.

07:50.121 --> 07:52.472
There's something
I want to show you.

07:56.780 --> 08:03.831
♪

08:13.841 --> 08:15.364
- What is this?

08:15.407 --> 08:20.064
- After you left,
I had a dream of you flying,

08:20.108 --> 08:22.676
only it wasn't the boy
that I knew.

08:22.719 --> 08:26.506
It was you now, so I made this.

08:30.640 --> 08:33.164
- Mom...

08:33.208 --> 08:35.515
leaving you after dad died...

08:35.558 --> 08:37.255
- Oh, honey,

08:37.299 --> 08:39.214
it's what you needed
to do then,

08:39.257 --> 08:42.086
and this is what
you need to do now.

08:42.130 --> 08:45.699
It's time for you
to go save the world, Clark.

08:52.836 --> 08:56.492
Still needs something
on the chest, I think.

08:58.625 --> 09:00.235
- Uh, pardon me, ma'am?
Ma'am?

09:00.278 --> 09:01.584
Do you know
where Milledge Avenue is?

09:01.628 --> 09:03.891
Milledge Avenue.
Milledge Avenue.

09:03.934 --> 09:05.719
Oh, excuse me, sir.
Excuse me.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.677
Do you know
where Milledge Avenue is?

09:11.202 --> 09:12.682
[tires squealing]

09:12.726 --> 09:15.076
- The brakes are out!
I can't stop!

09:15.119 --> 09:16.643
- It's a red light.
Swerve around!

09:16.686 --> 09:18.906
- There are people!
- Watch out!

09:18.949 --> 09:22.170
[dramatic music]

09:22.213 --> 09:29.264
♪

09:32.746 --> 09:34.835
[metal and glass crunch]

09:34.878 --> 09:40.318
♪

09:40.362 --> 09:41.668
- Whoa!
- Did you see that?

09:41.711 --> 09:45.019
[excited chatter]

09:51.852 --> 09:53.636
- There you go, friend.
- Thanks.

09:53.680 --> 09:54.855
Cool costume.

09:54.898 --> 09:57.597
- Thanks.
My mom made it for me.

09:57.640 --> 09:59.250
- Oh, my God.
- Whoa!

09:59.294 --> 10:01.818
- Did you see that?
- Yeah, right here. You'll see.

10:01.862 --> 10:04.647
[excited chatter]

10:04.691 --> 10:06.649
- Did you see that?
- See what?

10:06.693 --> 10:09.783
- Some guy just saved a kid
from getting killed by a car,

10:09.826 --> 10:11.654
and then he flew up
into the sky.

10:11.698 --> 10:12.916
- He flew?
- Flew, you know?

10:12.960 --> 10:14.657
Like a bird
or a plane or whatever.

10:14.701 --> 10:15.745
It was crazy.

10:15.789 --> 10:17.747
- Did you see
what he looked like?

10:17.791 --> 10:20.532
- He looked like a guy
in a cape that was flying.

10:20.576 --> 10:22.796
Someone at the "Planet"
has gotta hear about this.

10:22.839 --> 10:30.151
♪

10:37.724 --> 10:40.248
- This isn't a résumé.
It's a cry for help.

10:40.291 --> 10:42.206
- Oh, well--oh, oh.
Sorry.

10:42.250 --> 10:44.644
See, actually I did
some pretty top-notch reporting

10:44.687 --> 10:46.994
for my school paper.
- Look, this is Metropolis.

10:47.037 --> 10:49.431
I need cub reporters,
not lost puppies.

10:49.474 --> 10:51.694
You come find me when you got
some real world experience.

10:51.738 --> 10:53.565
- Oh, no, no, Mr. White,
Mr. White, please, look.

10:53.609 --> 10:54.915
I'm a really quick learner,

10:54.958 --> 10:56.177
and I'll do whatever you ask.

10:56.220 --> 10:58.309
I just--I just need a chance.

10:59.789 --> 11:01.661
- Okay,
there's no health insurance

11:01.704 --> 11:03.488
or overtime.
- Not a problem.

11:03.532 --> 11:05.882
- And you have to pick up
my dry cleaning every Thursday.

11:05.926 --> 11:07.405
- Yeah, absolutely.
Yes, sir.

11:08.232 --> 11:11.496
- Okay, kid, you're hired.
Now, try to keep up.

11:11.540 --> 11:14.412
- Oh, okay.
Do you want--should I--okay.

11:14.456 --> 11:15.500
Yeah, it's--

11:16.980 --> 11:18.982
- Everyone in here, we're
the most dependable friends

11:19.026 --> 11:20.810
the people of Metropolis have.

11:20.854 --> 11:22.290
You remember that.
- Yes, sir.

11:22.333 --> 11:25.423
- Stick with Lane.
She'll show you the ropes.

11:25.467 --> 11:26.860
- Lane, sir?

11:26.903 --> 11:28.949
- Who told you to wear a tie?

11:28.992 --> 11:31.952
[tender music]

11:31.995 --> 11:34.868
♪

11:34.911 --> 11:37.697
Let me guess, Lombard?
Ignore him.

11:37.740 --> 11:40.438
Though he can get box seats
to the Meteors.

11:40.482 --> 11:42.789
You like baseball?
- Uh, of course.

11:42.832 --> 11:45.313
I mean, who doesn't like
America's pastime, Ms. Lane?

11:45.356 --> 11:46.444
- It's Lois.

11:46.488 --> 11:47.837
What'd you say
your name was again?

11:47.881 --> 11:49.883
- Kent. Clark. Clark Kent.

11:49.926 --> 11:53.147
Oh, oh, sorry.

11:53.190 --> 11:55.976
- Hm, never met a Clark before.

11:56.019 --> 11:58.935
- Oh, I've never met
a Lois before.

11:58.979 --> 12:01.068
Actually, there was
my first-grade teacher,

12:01.111 --> 12:02.591
Lois Hannigan,
so I guess technically--

12:02.634 --> 12:04.332
oh, technically
you'd be the second.

12:05.637 --> 12:07.683
You know, Miss Hannigan was
actually my favorite teacher.

12:07.727 --> 12:09.859
She--she taught me
about fractions and cursive.

12:09.903 --> 12:12.949
- Mystery man strikes again.
Third time this month.

12:12.993 --> 12:14.081
- Where was he?

12:14.124 --> 12:15.952
- Saved a boat
sinking off Hob's River.

12:15.996 --> 12:17.214
Jimmy even got a photo.

12:17.258 --> 12:20.043
This is my Pulitzer, Lane.
I can feel it.

12:21.349 --> 12:23.003
- Seems like
a pretty big story.

12:23.046 --> 12:24.918
- Yeah,
which every reporter here

12:24.961 --> 12:27.877
is tripping over themselves
to cover.

12:27.921 --> 12:29.313
Boys and their heroes.

12:29.357 --> 12:31.794
- [chuckles]
Aren't heroes a good thing?

12:31.838 --> 12:33.665
- Yeah, of course, and I know
that we need this guy.

12:33.709 --> 12:35.145
It's just that
ever since he showed up,

12:35.189 --> 12:37.278
he's been dominating
the conversation.

12:37.321 --> 12:38.932
Metropolis has so many problems

12:38.975 --> 12:41.021
that aren't just
rescue operations.

12:41.064 --> 12:44.198
They're systemic.
Here, look at this.

12:47.854 --> 12:50.030
- These lightning bolts.
- Nazi symbols.

12:50.073 --> 12:52.467
They've been popping up
all over lower Metropolis

12:52.510 --> 12:54.599
along with a rash
of arson attacks

12:54.643 --> 12:56.340
against
minority-owned businesses.

12:56.384 --> 12:58.821
- Do you have any idea
who's responsible?

12:58.865 --> 13:00.997
- By all accounts, some psycho

13:01.041 --> 13:02.869
in a metal mask
and a trench coat.

13:02.912 --> 13:04.653
[soft dramatic music]

13:04.696 --> 13:07.308
- I didn't know about this.
- That's my point exactly.

13:07.351 --> 13:09.049
I have been covering this
for months,

13:09.092 --> 13:11.051
only my reporting
keeps getting drowned out

13:11.094 --> 13:13.053
by everyone's favorite
miracle man.

13:15.098 --> 13:16.578
- How can I help?

13:16.621 --> 13:19.581
[dramatic music]

13:19.624 --> 13:26.675
♪

13:28.285 --> 13:30.853
- Psycho in a metal mask
and a trench coat?

13:30.897 --> 13:33.508
That sounds--
sir, I'm listening to you.

13:35.466 --> 13:38.121
[indistinct radio chatter]

13:38.165 --> 13:42.778
♪

13:42.822 --> 13:44.258
- Whoo!

13:44.301 --> 13:44.998
Yes!

13:45.041 --> 13:48.349
[applause]

13:50.046 --> 13:52.092
- Clark, Clark,
I gotta show you something.

13:52.135 --> 13:53.789
- Well, I gotta get these
to Perry before he goes home.

13:53.833 --> 13:57.793
- Guess who was just arrested?
- Oh.

13:57.837 --> 14:04.844
♪

14:11.546 --> 14:14.288
- You don't need that.
- Wait--oh, no, I gotta--

14:14.331 --> 14:16.943
okay.

14:16.986 --> 14:18.814
- One of these dirt bags
is our guy.

14:18.858 --> 14:20.207
I can feel it.

14:22.122 --> 14:24.602
- You're really good at this.

14:26.735 --> 14:27.954
- Thanks.

14:33.046 --> 14:36.788
- I, um...I should get going.

14:38.660 --> 14:39.879
- What's the hurry.

14:41.054 --> 14:42.969
You got a big date?
- [chuckles]

14:43.012 --> 14:44.231
No, no, nothing like that.

14:44.274 --> 14:48.191
Just, you know,
some "Seinfeld" reruns.

14:48.235 --> 14:51.238
Heat up some
frozen chicken nuggets.

14:52.413 --> 14:54.981
- You've been
a really big help, Clark.

14:55.024 --> 14:57.331
If you want,
I can probably talk to Perry

14:57.374 --> 14:59.246
about you getting
a beat of your own,

14:59.289 --> 15:01.030
local politics or something.

15:01.074 --> 15:05.078
- Oh. Um...no.

15:05.121 --> 15:08.733
That's--it's okay.
I'd rather be here.

15:09.473 --> 15:12.172
- For the story or the company?

15:12.215 --> 15:14.217
- Uh...
[laughs]

15:14.261 --> 15:17.525
I feel like
that's a trick question.

15:19.744 --> 15:23.052
- Good night, Clark.
- Good night, Lois.

15:23.096 --> 15:26.055
[soft dramatic music]

15:26.099 --> 15:32.540
♪

15:43.116 --> 15:44.334
You seen Lois?

15:44.378 --> 15:46.380
- Her contact at the library
called back

15:46.423 --> 15:48.817
about some guy who works
at a hardware store.

15:55.084 --> 15:57.869
- Henry Miller?
- Hmm.

15:59.132 --> 16:01.830
[indistinct radio chatter]

16:01.873 --> 16:05.181
- You can't do this, Henry.
They've done nothing wrong.

16:05.225 --> 16:07.314
- They don't belong here.

16:07.357 --> 16:10.317
[explosion]
[people screaming]

16:10.360 --> 16:12.536
[dramatic music]

16:12.580 --> 16:14.277
- This isn't
track and field, Kent!

16:14.321 --> 16:16.062
♪

16:16.105 --> 16:18.847
- These people
have stolen my neighborhood,

16:18.890 --> 16:22.024
and you're spinning it
like I'm the bad guy?

16:22.068 --> 16:23.808
I'm the damn hero!

16:23.852 --> 16:30.902
♪

16:34.210 --> 16:37.170
[soft dramatic music]

16:37.213 --> 16:44.003
♪

16:51.836 --> 16:54.796
[dramatic music]

16:54.839 --> 16:56.450
♪

16:56.493 --> 16:58.669
- Even you can't save
all of them.

16:58.713 --> 17:05.546
♪

17:16.122 --> 17:17.993
- [groans]

17:19.255 --> 17:21.257
- Who's the hero now?

17:21.301 --> 17:24.260
[applause]

17:24.304 --> 17:27.263
[soft triumphant music]

17:27.307 --> 17:30.614
♪

17:30.658 --> 17:32.747
How'd you know about this?

17:32.790 --> 17:34.879
[sirens wailing]

17:34.923 --> 17:37.273
- I've been reading
your reports in the "Planet,"

17:37.317 --> 17:39.797
but also my hearing.

17:39.841 --> 17:41.277
- Your hearing?

17:41.321 --> 17:42.191
- Oh.
[chuckles]

17:42.235 --> 17:45.107
My super-hearing.

17:45.151 --> 17:47.675
- We haven't formally met.
I'm Lois Lane.

17:47.718 --> 17:49.242
- It's nice to meet you,
Ms. Lane.

17:49.285 --> 17:51.418
- And you are who exactly?

17:51.461 --> 17:55.248
Mister Metropolis?
Red and Blue Man?

17:55.291 --> 17:56.858
- [chuckles]

17:56.901 --> 17:59.034
I'm sure
you'll come up with something.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.993
♪

18:02.037 --> 18:05.127
[crowd gasping]

18:07.260 --> 18:11.568
- Who was that?
- Superman.

18:15.920 --> 18:18.358
[bright music]

18:18.401 --> 18:20.142
- Welcome
to the "Daily Planet Today."

18:20.186 --> 18:22.362
I'm Lois Lane,
and with me for his first

18:22.405 --> 18:25.408
on-camera interview
is Superman.

18:25.452 --> 18:27.149
I appreciate you
agreeing to be here.

18:27.193 --> 18:28.759
- Thanks for having me.

18:28.803 --> 18:30.761
- Now, as you know, the world
has been captivated by you

18:30.805 --> 18:32.763
ever since your first
appearance in Metropolis

18:32.807 --> 18:35.288
over a year ago,
and one of the big questions

18:35.331 --> 18:37.203
that always gets asked
regarding Superman

18:37.246 --> 18:40.206
is how long you were
on Earth before that.

18:40.249 --> 18:42.077
- Well,
essentially my whole life.

18:42.121 --> 18:44.645
After my planet was destroyed--
- Krypton.

18:44.688 --> 18:47.256
- Right,
when Krypton was destroyed,

18:47.300 --> 18:49.171
the pod that allowed me
to escape

18:49.215 --> 18:50.520
crashed here on Earth.

18:50.564 --> 18:52.740
- Where exactly on Earth?

18:52.783 --> 18:54.829
- That's not something
I'm ready to reveal yet.

18:54.872 --> 18:57.136
- The assumption is that
it was somewhere in the U.S.

18:57.179 --> 19:00.139
- Well, don't assume that just
because I'm speaking English.

19:02.663 --> 19:04.969
- You speak multiple languages.
Is that also a superpower?

19:05.013 --> 19:06.232
- [laughs]
No.

19:06.275 --> 19:08.451
Just curiosity about the world.

19:08.495 --> 19:10.323
I wanted to know more
about different people,

19:10.366 --> 19:14.240
different regions,
so I studied their languages.

19:14.283 --> 19:15.632
- How many languages?

19:17.025 --> 19:18.244
- All of them.

19:20.289 --> 19:22.248
- What would you say
to the people of the world

19:22.291 --> 19:24.641
when asked what you stand for?

19:26.339 --> 19:29.342
- I'd like to think
everything good and decent.

19:29.385 --> 19:31.605
Truth, justice.

19:31.648 --> 19:33.607
- The American way?

19:33.650 --> 19:35.826
- [chuckles]
I think someone's just trying

19:35.870 --> 19:37.567
to get me to admit
I was raised here.

19:37.611 --> 19:40.309
[microphone feedback squeaks]

19:40.353 --> 19:42.093
- Cut!

19:42.137 --> 19:44.226
Can someone please
take a look at Lois' mic?

19:44.270 --> 19:45.880
- All right, everybody,
let's stand by

19:45.923 --> 19:47.403
for sound check.
Stand by please.

19:47.447 --> 19:49.013
- I feel like
we're not getting anywhere.

19:49.057 --> 19:50.319
- I can't believe it.

19:50.363 --> 19:52.234
- No, I know, he's, like,
giving me the runaround.

19:52.278 --> 19:56.978
- No, not that.
I think Superman is into you.

19:58.197 --> 19:59.502
- Don't be ridiculous.

19:59.546 --> 20:01.330
- The way
he keeps smiling at you?

20:01.374 --> 20:03.202
I dream of having someone
look at me like that.

20:03.245 --> 20:05.378
It's basically how
all my favorite movies end.

20:05.421 --> 20:08.729
- Janet, he's Superman.
It's part of his whole shtick.

20:08.772 --> 20:10.470
He looks at people
in a nice way.

20:10.513 --> 20:13.734
- Okay, listen, I'm not talking
to you as your producer.

20:13.777 --> 20:15.344
I'm talking to you
as one of your best friends.

20:15.388 --> 20:17.041
And I am telling you...
- Janet.

20:17.085 --> 20:19.305
- There is some
serious chemistry happening...

20:19.348 --> 20:20.523
- Listen to me.

20:20.567 --> 20:22.046
- And you need
to bring your A game

20:22.090 --> 20:23.439
if you wanna go out

20:23.483 --> 20:24.397
with the world's
most eligible bachelor.

20:24.440 --> 20:26.529
- I am not interested, okay?

20:26.573 --> 20:28.531
I'm in love with someone else.

20:30.577 --> 20:32.753
Clark from the paper.

20:32.796 --> 20:34.624
We've been dating
for a couple months.

20:34.668 --> 20:36.496
I know he's dorky,
but I love him.

20:36.539 --> 20:39.150
- Right,
the guy with the glasses.

20:39.194 --> 20:40.282
- Yeah.
- He's so sweet.

20:40.326 --> 20:41.892
- Yeah.
- Well, that's great, Lois.

20:41.936 --> 20:44.286
I--I had no idea
you were in love.

20:44.330 --> 20:47.333
- That's because I haven't
told anyone yet, not even him.

20:47.376 --> 20:49.596
[tender music]

20:49.639 --> 20:51.728
- Hey, random
Superman question.

20:51.772 --> 20:53.991
He wouldn't happen
to have super-hearing?

20:54.035 --> 21:01.085
♪

21:02.913 --> 21:04.350
- [whispers]
Can we just go?

21:04.393 --> 21:06.308
- [whispers]
Yeah, yeah.

21:11.574 --> 21:13.663
- [clears throat]
I apologize.

21:13.707 --> 21:15.622
That was unprofessional.

21:15.665 --> 21:19.060
- That's okay.
He's a--he's a lucky man.

21:19.103 --> 21:21.758
- Don't think this means
I'm gonna take it easy on you.

21:21.802 --> 21:24.239
- I'd be offended if you did.
- Okay.

21:24.283 --> 21:25.414
Ready?

21:25.458 --> 21:26.807
I'm nervous.

21:26.850 --> 21:29.026
- I didn't think
you got nervous.

21:29.070 --> 21:30.898
- Well, it's your mom, Clark.
What if she doesn't like me?

21:30.941 --> 21:32.595
- [laughs]
That's not possible.

21:32.639 --> 21:34.554
- Maybe you haven't seen
the reader mail section

21:34.597 --> 21:37.470
of the newspaper, but trust me,
it's very possible.

21:37.513 --> 21:38.558
Hi.

21:38.601 --> 21:42.126
- Oh, I'm so glad
you could make it.

21:42.170 --> 21:45.521
Oh, look at you.
[laughs]

21:45.565 --> 21:48.176
Ever since Clark told me
about the two of you,

21:48.219 --> 21:50.221
I couldn't wait
to have you out to the farm.

21:50.265 --> 21:51.571
- Told you.

21:51.614 --> 21:53.355
- Well, I'm happy
to finally make it.

21:53.399 --> 21:54.922
- Oh, thank you.

21:54.965 --> 21:58.012
Lots of folks in Smallville
are dying to meet you too.

21:58.055 --> 22:00.057
- Mom, Mom, Mom, you promised.
- Oh, Clark.

22:00.101 --> 22:01.972
It's just the neighbors
and Edelsteins

22:02.016 --> 22:04.453
and, you know,
girls from bridge club, so...

22:04.497 --> 22:06.368
- Well, I'm very excited
to meet everyone.

22:06.412 --> 22:09.589
- Well, come on inside.
I've got lunch waiting.

22:09.632 --> 22:16.378
♪

22:16.422 --> 22:18.206
She's wonderful.

22:18.249 --> 22:20.295
- Yeah, I know.

22:20.339 --> 22:23.124
- So what took you so long
to bring her here?

22:23.167 --> 22:27.389
- Because I needed to be ready.
- To meet me?

22:27.433 --> 22:29.173
- That's not what I meant.

22:30.697 --> 22:35.484
I brought her here to tell her
who I really am.

22:36.790 --> 22:38.705
- Oh, are you sure?

22:38.748 --> 22:40.663
Once you tell her,
there's no going back.

22:40.707 --> 22:43.492
- Yeah, well...

22:43.536 --> 22:46.321
there was no going back
after the first time I saw her.

22:46.365 --> 22:49.237
- I'm so happy for you, honey.

22:51.544 --> 22:53.502
- Everything okay?

22:53.546 --> 22:57.071
- Everything's perfect, dear.
Just perfect.

22:58.638 --> 23:01.641
- You follow me.
I wanna show you something.

23:01.684 --> 23:04.426
[tender orchestral music]

23:04.470 --> 23:11.781
♪

23:23.314 --> 23:30.365
♪

23:36.806 --> 23:39.374
[crowd cheering]
- Love you, Lois!

23:39.418 --> 23:42.246
Love you, Clark!

23:42.290 --> 23:44.640
- I can't believe
I married Lois Lane.

23:46.990 --> 23:50.559
- I'm all yours, babe.
For better or for worse.

23:52.692 --> 23:53.997
- You know, I...

23:55.956 --> 23:59.873
I kept my secret
from everyone for so long,

23:59.916 --> 24:01.831
and now I know why.

24:04.704 --> 24:06.183
It's for you.

24:07.228 --> 24:10.449
So we could have
this life together.

24:12.755 --> 24:15.410
- There's no one
I'd rather share it with.

24:16.411 --> 24:18.065
- This might be
a weird time to say it,

24:18.108 --> 24:21.547
but I can't wait to tell my dad
about the wedding.

24:21.590 --> 24:23.897
He's gonna be so excited.

24:23.940 --> 24:27.857
I mean, as excited
as a hologram can get, I guess.

24:27.901 --> 24:30.686
- Well, he's gonna have to wait
till after the honeymoon.

24:30.730 --> 24:33.515
[tender music]

24:33.559 --> 24:38.346
♪

24:38.389 --> 24:41.480
- How was
your marriage ceremony, son?

24:42.568 --> 24:43.830
- It was the perfect day.

24:43.873 --> 24:45.614
Lois looked beautiful.

24:45.658 --> 24:47.094
I wish
you could have been there.

24:47.137 --> 24:49.183
- I need you
to get out of here now, Son.

24:49.226 --> 24:51.011
[eerie music]

24:51.054 --> 24:53.404
- Father, what's happening?
- Go!

24:53.448 --> 24:54.971
♪

24:55.015 --> 24:57.408
Get out of here now!

24:57.452 --> 25:00.411
[dramatic music]

25:00.455 --> 25:01.891
♪

25:05.068 --> 25:07.723
[soft dramatic music]

25:07.767 --> 25:10.900
- Hey, babe, there's something
I need to tell you.

25:10.944 --> 25:13.337
- Lois, what day is it?
- I'm pregnant.

25:15.252 --> 25:17.690
- You're pregnant?
- Yes.

25:17.733 --> 25:19.474
I know, we weren't even trying.

25:19.518 --> 25:20.867
We didn't even know
this was possible,

25:20.910 --> 25:22.651
but there are
three pregnancy tests

25:22.695 --> 25:24.871
in the bathroom, and they all
say the same thing.

25:26.612 --> 25:28.265
We're gonna be parents.

25:29.223 --> 25:31.181
- Okay, Lois, something
really strange happened

25:31.225 --> 25:34.054
right before you came out.
- I can't believe it either.

25:34.097 --> 25:36.056
It's like you said
on our honeymoon.

25:36.099 --> 25:38.624
This is why
you kept your secret.

25:38.667 --> 25:40.756
- So we can share
our life together.

25:40.800 --> 25:43.150
- And now we can have a family.

25:43.193 --> 25:44.978
I didn't even realize
I wanted one

25:45.021 --> 25:47.458
this badly until now.

25:47.502 --> 25:49.809
- Yeah. Yeah, me too.

25:49.852 --> 25:51.941
- Okay, be honest,
you want a boy or a girl?

25:51.985 --> 25:54.422
- I--I just want the baby
to be healthy.

25:54.465 --> 25:55.815
- Come on, Clark.
That's so predictable.

25:55.858 --> 25:57.381
- What?
It's true.

25:57.425 --> 25:58.774
- All right,
well, I'm just gonna say it.

25:58.818 --> 26:00.646
I want a girl.
- Okay.

26:00.689 --> 26:01.734
- Okay.

26:05.389 --> 26:08.175
- Oh, my.
- Is everything okay?

26:08.218 --> 26:11.613
- Yes, it's just more okay.

26:14.007 --> 26:15.835
Looks like you two
are going to have twins.

26:15.878 --> 26:17.140
- What?
Are you sure?

26:17.184 --> 26:18.968
- Ooh, is that a--you know?

26:19.012 --> 26:20.883
- Very,
and I can't say for certain,

26:20.927 --> 26:24.147
but, yes,
they do appear to be boys.

26:24.191 --> 26:26.410
- This is what I get
for wanting a girl.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.456
- I can't believe I'm gonna
be a dad twice all at once.

26:28.499 --> 26:31.764
- Can you get me
some water, please?

26:31.807 --> 26:33.592
- Babe.

26:33.635 --> 26:34.897
♪

26:34.941 --> 26:36.769
- Do you think
this is because of Superman?

26:36.812 --> 26:39.641
- My father assured me
everything's gonna be fine.

26:39.685 --> 26:41.208
- He also didn't know
we were having twins,

26:41.251 --> 26:42.731
and that is
a pretty big curve ball.

26:42.775 --> 26:45.473
- Hey, it's gonna be okay.
I promise.

26:45.516 --> 26:47.301
- Yeah, says the guy
who doesn't have to give birth

26:47.344 --> 26:48.868
to two babies at the same time.

26:48.911 --> 26:50.217
- [chuckles]

26:53.612 --> 26:56.571
[eerie music]

26:56.615 --> 27:03.317
♪

27:03.360 --> 27:06.799
Clark, I'm not delivering
the babies at the fortress.

27:06.842 --> 27:11.630
♪

27:11.673 --> 27:13.370
- This isn't real.

27:13.414 --> 27:16.373
[dramatic music]

27:16.417 --> 27:20.377
♪

27:20.421 --> 27:22.641
- In a lifetime
full of memories,

27:22.684 --> 27:24.773
there is none more special
than becoming a father.

27:24.817 --> 27:26.819
♪

27:26.862 --> 27:29.343
- What have you done?
- Easy, Kal-El.

27:29.386 --> 27:31.911
I'd hate for you
to miss the big moment.

27:31.954 --> 27:33.260
- [screams]
- You're doing great.

27:33.303 --> 27:37.612
We're almost there.
- Yeah, 27 hours later.

27:37.656 --> 27:40.136
- Edge is here somehow.
- I love you too.

27:40.180 --> 27:41.747
[screams]
- Just one more push, Lois,

27:41.790 --> 27:43.357
and baby Jonathan
can meet Jordan.

27:43.400 --> 27:46.839
- He knows everything.
- [screams]

27:46.882 --> 27:48.188
[baby crying]
- You did it!

27:48.231 --> 27:51.365
- We have a family, Clark.
- Yes, you do.

27:51.408 --> 27:54.455
[babies crying]

27:55.499 --> 27:57.023
Jordan and Jonathan Kent,

27:57.066 --> 28:00.200
the twin sons
of Lois and Superman.

28:00.243 --> 28:02.202
- No. No, please. Please.
They're just babies.

28:02.245 --> 28:04.770
- How little
you know me, brother.

28:04.813 --> 28:06.423
I would never harm a newborn.

28:06.467 --> 28:08.904
♪

28:08.948 --> 28:11.254
Teenage boys,
on the other hand...

28:11.864 --> 28:14.562
That's a different
matter entirely.

28:14.605 --> 28:21.308
♪

28:21.351 --> 28:24.137
It's good you're awake, Kal-El.

28:24.180 --> 28:27.749
Now you and I can discuss
the terms of your surrender.

28:34.887 --> 28:38.760
- My sons
are not bargaining chips.

28:38.804 --> 28:41.545
[soft dramatic music]

28:41.589 --> 28:43.983
- This device
was created by Ter-Loc,

28:44.026 --> 28:46.420
one of Krypton's
greatest scientists.

28:46.463 --> 28:50.424
It allows the user to navigate
the resting mind of another.

28:50.467 --> 28:53.166
- You knew I'd be weak
from my solar flare.

28:53.209 --> 28:55.081
- So I followed you here

28:55.124 --> 28:58.737
where I could sift through
your most precious memories.

29:00.826 --> 29:04.917
- To extort me?
- No, Kal, to understand you.

29:04.960 --> 29:07.006
To understand
what possible reason

29:07.049 --> 29:08.921
you could have
to betray your heritage.

29:08.964 --> 29:11.619
And to think it was all
for a human family.

29:11.662 --> 29:14.361
- You know nothing about them.
- I know enough.

29:14.404 --> 29:18.234
A human wife and twin boys.
How woefully pedestrian.

29:18.278 --> 29:20.846
And you, stumbling
through your daily life

29:20.889 --> 29:21.977
like some village idiot

29:22.021 --> 29:23.849
instead of a true son
of Krypton.

29:23.892 --> 29:26.634
- I'm not the only one who kept
my Kryptonian side hidden.

29:26.677 --> 29:30.029
- I did so out of strategy,
not shame.

29:30.072 --> 29:33.989
To be a man of greatness
and choose to be less...

29:34.033 --> 29:35.382
[chuckles]

29:35.425 --> 29:38.037
It speaks to the mediocrity
of this world.

29:38.080 --> 29:40.909
- Whatever it is you want,

29:40.953 --> 29:44.783
threatening my family
is not how you'll get it.

29:44.826 --> 29:46.132
- It's not a threat, Kal.

29:46.175 --> 29:49.222
I will destroy their lives
by taking that thing

29:49.265 --> 29:51.267
you hold so dear, your secret,

29:51.311 --> 29:53.269
and shouting it
for all the world to hear.

29:53.313 --> 29:55.924
Superman has a family.
- No!

29:55.968 --> 29:58.100
- Then tell me another way.

29:58.144 --> 30:00.755
I appealed to you as a brother,
and you attacked me,

30:00.799 --> 30:02.888
a Kryptonian,
and you stole from me,

30:02.931 --> 30:05.804
a friend, and you destroyed
everything I had built.

30:05.847 --> 30:09.068
- He is none of those things.
Do not listen to him!

30:09.111 --> 30:13.289
- It is this man
who has corrupted you,

30:13.333 --> 30:15.509
just as he
corrupted our mother.

30:17.250 --> 30:20.862
- I spoke with her. Lara.

30:20.906 --> 30:23.996
She believes
there is still good in you.

30:24.997 --> 30:26.781
- Was this
as she helped you plot

30:26.825 --> 30:28.261
to destroy Kryptonian lives?

30:28.304 --> 30:30.263
- The same lives that occupied

30:30.306 --> 30:31.699
innocent human beings?

30:31.742 --> 30:33.005
- Enough!

30:33.048 --> 30:36.660
I will not debate morality
with this whisper.

30:39.098 --> 30:40.969
Here I stand, brother.

30:41.013 --> 30:43.885
Flesh and bone
and beating heart.

30:43.929 --> 30:47.106
Your true family.

30:47.149 --> 30:50.631
Join me of your own free will.

30:50.674 --> 30:52.111
[dramatic music]

30:52.154 --> 30:54.983
- I can't let you do this.

30:55.027 --> 30:58.030
- Then I will make you suffer.

30:58.073 --> 31:00.032
♪

31:00.075 --> 31:03.383
[glass cracking]

31:05.951 --> 31:08.257
- I love you, son.

31:11.130 --> 31:18.441
♪

31:23.316 --> 31:26.145
- You are my life's greatest
disappointment, Kal-El.

31:26.188 --> 31:28.016
All my life, I dreamt

31:28.060 --> 31:31.324
of having a brother, a family,

31:31.367 --> 31:33.543
only to have you reject me!

31:33.587 --> 31:39.549
♪

31:39.593 --> 31:41.812
It didn't have to be this way.

31:41.856 --> 31:48.907
♪

31:57.089 --> 32:00.440
- This head is pounding worse
than after ten whiskey chasers.

32:00.483 --> 32:01.963
- From everything we can tell,

32:02.007 --> 32:04.052
it should go away
in a day or two.

32:04.096 --> 32:06.185
- How's Emily doing?

32:06.228 --> 32:09.057
- Confused. Overwhelmed.

32:09.101 --> 32:10.450
- What's she know, exactly?

32:10.493 --> 32:13.018
- Just the broad strokes,
same as everyone else.

32:13.061 --> 32:14.802
Edge was giving people powers,

32:14.845 --> 32:16.586
messing with their minds
to control them.

32:16.630 --> 32:18.937
- Nothing about
alien consciousness?

32:18.980 --> 32:22.157
- DOD felt that would be
better kept off the record.

32:22.201 --> 32:24.594
- Still a lot to process.

32:24.638 --> 32:28.337
And people in this town
are gonna want answers.

32:28.381 --> 32:30.992
- Yeah, at which point
they're gonna be looking

32:31.036 --> 32:33.777
for someone to blame,
and pretty sure

32:33.821 --> 32:35.518
I'm gonna be
at the top of that list.

32:36.911 --> 32:39.131
- Your heart was
in the right place, babe.

32:39.174 --> 32:40.654
- Heart's not the problems.

32:40.697 --> 32:45.006
It's this stubborn head of mine
refusing to listen.

32:45.050 --> 32:48.009
I should've never gone
to see Edge behind your back.

32:48.053 --> 32:50.316
[tender music]

32:50.359 --> 32:53.536
- Speaking of Edge,
any idea where he went?

32:53.580 --> 32:56.409
- Superman and the DOD
are looking for him.

32:56.452 --> 32:58.280
I'm sure he'll turn up soon.

32:58.324 --> 33:00.239
- It's like a war zone downtown

33:00.282 --> 33:02.023
with all
of the military patrolling.

33:02.067 --> 33:04.417
It's very end of days.

33:04.460 --> 33:06.201
- I think Grandpa said
they're gonna be leaving soon.

33:06.245 --> 33:07.811
They just have to check in

33:07.855 --> 33:10.292
on everybody that was
mind-swapped or whatever.

33:10.336 --> 33:13.339
- My dad has his good side
and his not-so-good side,

33:13.382 --> 33:18.257
but seeing him become
a whole different person is--

33:18.300 --> 33:20.737
- Must've been strange.
- Super weird.

33:20.781 --> 33:24.785
- I just instantly assumed
the worst about him,

33:24.828 --> 33:28.310
even though my mom told me
that it wasn't all his fault.

33:28.354 --> 33:30.356
- Well, sometimes
it's hard to tell

33:30.399 --> 33:32.053
when parents are
telling you the truth.

33:32.097 --> 33:34.838
- It's probably the same
for them, you know, with us.

33:34.882 --> 33:37.232
It seems like families
are always lying to each other,

33:37.276 --> 33:40.192
which is pretty messed up.

33:40.235 --> 33:44.196
So thank you for being honest
with me about everything.

33:44.239 --> 33:46.067
- Yeah.
Yeah, sure.

33:46.111 --> 33:48.591
Just--I'm sorry it was a--

33:48.635 --> 33:50.637
sorry it was such
a traumatic experience.

33:50.680 --> 33:52.421
- At least it was the truth.

33:54.902 --> 33:58.862
Is it cool if I have
a moment alone with Jordan?

34:00.255 --> 34:02.779
- Yeah.
Yeah, sure.

34:09.830 --> 34:11.832
- Sarah, I--I'm so sorry

34:11.875 --> 34:13.660
I didn't tell you everything
that was happening.

34:13.703 --> 34:15.270
John even wanted me
to tell you,

34:15.314 --> 34:18.099
and I--I said no.
I was really scared.

34:18.143 --> 34:19.187
I--

34:19.231 --> 34:24.410
♪

34:24.453 --> 34:29.023
- I don't want to be
just friends anymore.

34:30.372 --> 34:31.982
- Me neither.

34:32.026 --> 34:38.859
♪

34:43.255 --> 34:45.344
- Uh, Lois,

34:45.387 --> 34:48.956
hold--hold up
just a--just a second.

34:48.999 --> 34:51.001
Um...

34:51.045 --> 34:54.353
Listen, I just--
I wanted to apologize to you,

34:54.396 --> 34:56.094
you know, for the way
I've treated you

34:56.137 --> 34:57.660
this whole time.

34:57.704 --> 35:00.141
- It's okay, Kyle.
- No. No, it's not.

35:01.186 --> 35:05.407
Look, I was wrong about--
about damn near everything,

35:05.451 --> 35:09.933
but...mostly,
I was wrong about you.

35:09.977 --> 35:12.632
You're good people, Lois,

35:12.675 --> 35:14.938
and I'm real happy
you're part of this town.

35:16.114 --> 35:17.376
- Thank you.

35:27.299 --> 35:31.172
- So it's, like,
really official official now

35:31.216 --> 35:32.695
or what?

35:32.739 --> 35:34.697
- Yeah, I guess so.
- Yeah?

35:34.741 --> 35:36.786
- Well, I'm happy
for you, sweetie,

35:36.830 --> 35:38.658
but now that you
have a girlfriend,

35:38.701 --> 35:40.312
your dad and I
are gonna have to have

35:40.355 --> 35:42.357
a little chitchat
with you about what we expect.

35:42.401 --> 35:44.185
[whooshes]

35:44.229 --> 35:45.230
- Guess Dad's home.

35:46.492 --> 35:48.320
[ominous music]

35:48.363 --> 35:50.452
- Your father won't be
returning any time soon,

35:50.496 --> 35:53.977
which is why Uncle Morgan
decided to come pay a visit.

35:59.069 --> 36:01.289
- So this is the life
Kal-El chose.

36:01.333 --> 36:04.379
It's even more
disappointing up close.

36:04.423 --> 36:05.728
- You're not welcome here.

36:05.772 --> 36:09.384
- That's no way
to speak to family, Lois,

36:09.428 --> 36:11.125
especially
with young boys around.

36:11.169 --> 36:12.431
- Where's our dad?

36:12.474 --> 36:14.302
- When I left him,
he was a crumpled heap

36:14.346 --> 36:15.564
in his little ice castle.

36:15.608 --> 36:17.392
Peculiar place
to build a fortress.

36:17.436 --> 36:18.959
I chose the desert.

36:19.002 --> 36:21.396
Like to feel the sun
on my face.

36:22.571 --> 36:25.531
- Leave, now.
- Jordan, stop.

36:25.574 --> 36:28.490
- Oh, I see your son's
inherited your false bravado.

36:28.534 --> 36:31.624
[dramatic music]

36:31.667 --> 36:32.973
- Jordan!

36:34.017 --> 36:37.325
- Stay away from my sons!
- This is all your doing.

36:37.369 --> 36:39.066
It was your influence
that made him

36:39.109 --> 36:40.807
turn his back
on his own people.

36:40.850 --> 36:43.244
- Let them go.
This is between you and me.

36:43.288 --> 36:46.204
- I'm afraid we've passed
that point, Ms. Lane,

36:46.247 --> 36:50.251
but I will let them live
long enough to watch you die.

36:50.295 --> 36:53.036
[suspenseful music]

36:53.080 --> 36:56.214
♪

36:56.257 --> 36:59.608
Impressive, Kal-El.
But this changes nothing.

37:02.089 --> 37:06.441
- I'll do whatever you ask.
Just leave my family alone.

37:06.485 --> 37:09.444
[soft dramatic music]

37:09.488 --> 37:10.880
♪

37:10.924 --> 37:14.319
- Pledge to me
that you will submit,

37:14.362 --> 37:17.365
and I promise
to let them live unharmed.

37:17.409 --> 37:19.846
- Clark, please don't do this.

37:21.413 --> 37:23.153
- I submit.

37:27.027 --> 37:29.421
- Take a good look
at the man you knew,

37:29.464 --> 37:31.945
'cause it will be your last.

37:33.990 --> 37:36.210
- I'm sorry.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.559
We needed more time.

37:37.603 --> 37:39.909
♪

37:39.953 --> 37:41.607
He was right.

37:44.479 --> 37:47.439
[eerie music]

37:47.482 --> 37:54.402
♪

37:58.363 --> 38:01.409
- This is--
- My home.

38:01.453 --> 38:08.764
♪

38:11.027 --> 38:13.639
I'm ready, Father.

38:20.385 --> 38:27.392
♪

38:42.407 --> 38:45.105
- Finally.

38:45.148 --> 38:46.672
My son.

38:47.803 --> 38:50.502
What year is it on this Earth?

38:50.545 --> 38:52.765
- By their measurements, 1987.

38:52.808 --> 38:55.985
- And the Eradicator,
you possess it?

38:57.160 --> 38:58.553
- Not yet.

38:58.597 --> 39:01.339
- Did I birth a fool
for a son?

39:01.382 --> 39:03.341
Your mission was simple!

39:03.384 --> 39:06.561
- I've spent years searching,
but it is still yet to arrive.

39:08.171 --> 39:09.564
- I see.

39:09.608 --> 39:12.611
Well, we must prepare

39:12.654 --> 39:13.742
in the interim.

39:13.786 --> 39:15.744
I will train you myself.

39:15.788 --> 39:17.355
- Thank you, Father.

39:17.398 --> 39:19.835
- We must root out
all weakness

39:19.879 --> 39:23.839
so that you can gain power
in this world.

39:23.883 --> 39:27.147
- Were there any other
Kryptonians sent to join me?

39:27.190 --> 39:28.801
- [sighs]

39:28.844 --> 39:31.499
There's that weakness.

39:31.543 --> 39:33.458
You need no one, son.

39:33.501 --> 39:35.547
Only me. Is that understood?

39:35.590 --> 39:37.026
- Yes, sir.

39:37.070 --> 39:40.116
- The first lesson
is the measure of pain.

39:40.160 --> 39:44.643
Its application being a tool
of great strategic value.

39:44.686 --> 39:47.602
Although, in your case,

39:47.646 --> 39:52.085
it is necessary that you
be able to withstand it.

39:52.128 --> 39:54.261
♪

39:54.304 --> 39:56.959
- [screaming]

40:01.834 --> 40:05.925
Here he is, Father.
- Son of Jor-El.

40:05.968 --> 40:09.189
The worst of Krypton.

40:09.232 --> 40:13.106
- You don't have to do this.
- See how he begs?

40:13.149 --> 40:16.196
His own weakness
never stamped out.

40:16.239 --> 40:19.242
- He has vowed
his submission, Father.

40:19.286 --> 40:23.638
- And the Eradicator?
- Taken from his possession.

40:23.682 --> 40:26.685
- Then let us begin.

40:26.728 --> 40:29.688
[soft dramatic music]

40:29.731 --> 40:36.782
♪

40:50.186 --> 40:53.233
[device whirring]

40:55.670 --> 40:57.542
[dial tone trilling]

40:59.544 --> 41:02.634
- [groaning in pain]

41:02.677 --> 41:06.725
♪

41:06.768 --> 41:09.467
- John, it's happening.

41:09.510 --> 41:10.642
Just like you said it would.

41:10.685 --> 41:13.035
♪

41:13.079 --> 41:15.473
I think
Superman's been turned.

41:44.719 --> 41:46.721
- Greg, move your head.
